#Approach:

Approach:
Ye code smallest number banane ke liye monotonic increasing stack use karta hai.

1. Number ke digits ko left se right traverse karte hain.
2. Jab current digit stack ke top se chhota hota hai aur k > 0 hota hai,
   tab stack se bada digit pop kar dete hain.
   Kyuki left side par bada digit rehne se number bada banega.
3. Fir current digit ko stack me push kar dete hain.
4. Agar traverse ke baad bhi k bacha ho,
   to end ke digits pop kar dete hain, kyuki wo sabse less important hote hain.
5. Stack ke digits se final number banate hain.
6. Starting ke leading zeros hata dete hain.
7. Agar sab remove ho gaya ya sirf zeros bache, to answer "0" return karte hain.

Main idea:
Chhota number banane ke liye left side par possible minimum digit rakhna hota hai.
Isliye jab bhi koi smaller digit milta hai, usse pehle ke bigger digits hata dete hain.

Time Complexity: O(n)
Space Complexity: O(n)

#Code:

import java.util.Deque;
import java.util.ArrayDeque;

public class Solution {
    public String removeKdigits(String num, int k) {
        //You can code here

        int n = num.length();
        Deque<Integer> stack = new ArrayDeque<>();
        for(int i=0; i<n; i++){
          //case 1 if string digit is smaller than stack's peak element
          while(!stack.isEmpty() && k > 0 && (stack.peek() > (num.charAt(i) - '0'))){
            stack.pop();
            k = k - 1;
          }
          //otherwise we just add that element in the stack
          stack.push(num.charAt(i) - '0');
        }

        while(k > 0){
          stack.pop();
          k = k - 1;
        }

        if(stack.isEmpty()) return "0";

        StringBuilder res = new StringBuilder();
        while(!stack.isEmpty()){
          res.append(stack.pop());
        }
        res.reverse();

        int idx = 0;
        while (idx < res.length() && res.charAt(idx) == '0') idx++;

        String ans = res.substring(idx);
        return ans.length() == 0 ? "0" : ans;
      
    }
}
